    h1 Data Table
    ul.docs-index
    p Data tables display sets of raw data. They usually appear in desktop enterprise products
    .with-device
      h2(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/core/data-table.html") Data Table Layout
      p Common Data Table layout could be treated as the following:
      :code(lang="html")
            <div class="data-table">
              <table>
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th class="label-cell">Desert (100g serving)</th>
                    <th class="numeric-cell">Calories</th>
                    ...
                    <th class="tablet-only">Comment</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="label-cell">Frozen yogurt</td>
                    <td class="numeric-cell">159</td>
                    ...
                    <td class="tablet-only">I like it!</td>
                  </tr>
                  ...
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
      p Within <a href="./cards.html">Card</a>:
      :code(lang="html")
            <div class="data-table card">
              <table>
                <thead>
                ...
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                ...
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
      p Where
      ul
        li <code>data-table</code> - main Data Table wrapper. Required
          ul
            li <code>table</code> - table itself. Required
              ul
                li <code>thead</code> - table head
                li <code>tbody</code> - table body. Required
                li <code>label-cell</code> - main label cell (only one such kind of cell per row, usually first cell)
                li <code>numeric-cell</code> - cell to display numeric data (right-aligned)
                li <code>tablet-only</code> - additional class to show this cell/column only on wide tablet devices (iPad)
