      h2(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/core/data-table-head-inputs.html") Inputs In Table Head
      p Such tables are widely used in admin interfaces for filtering or search data
      :code(lang="html")
            <div class="card data-table">
              <table>
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th class="input-cell">
                      <span class="table-head-label">ID</span>
                      <div class="input" style="width: 50px">
                        <input type="number" placeholder="Filter">
                      </div>
                    </th>
                    <th class="input-cell">
                      <span class="table-head-label">Name</span>
                      <div class="input">
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Filter">
                      </div>
                    </th>
                    ...
                    <th class="input-cell">
                      <span class="table-head-label">Gender</span>
                      <div class="input input-dropdown">
                        <select>
                          <option value="All">All</option>
                          <option value="Male">Male</option>
                          <option value="Female">Female</option>
                        </select>
                      </div>
                    </th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>1</td>
                    <td>John Doe</td>
                    <td>john@doe.com</td>
                    <td>Male</td>
                  </tr>
                  ...
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
      p Where
      ul
        li
          p <code>input-cell</code> - additional class on table cell required to display input
        li
          p <code>&lt;span class="table-head-label"&gt;</code> - input label
        li
          p <code>&lt;div class="input"&gt;</code> - input container

